It is a really unique and fun game so far a few hours in.. but what's the deal with the saves? I lose a lot of progress randomly when I restart app, even when it claims it saved seconds ago before that...

This is a lovely game. The pixel graphics take me straight back to the olden days, when I'd just started gaming. It's well thought out. And you kinda get attached to the dogs, as you get to know 'em. However, it has some litte issues. For example: I expand my kennel from 4 to 6, the game crashes, I come back on, only to find my kennel isn't being expanded anymore and yet the 8k money has gone. Oopsie. Other than tiny and also rare things, superb game and well worth it imo.

After wading through a sea of garbage IAP, pay-to-win, spam your friends games that flood the market it's so refreshing to see a game that is so simple, addictive and fun. Best of all it doesn't ask for a dime after the initial purchase.  The game is an rpg at it's heart but instead of managing a team of fighters, it's a pack of dogs. Each one can be micromanaged to control their levels of exhaustion, happiness and skill.   The battling happens on the race track where you compete against other sledders (CPU

I could not have enough good things to say about this game at first it took me a long time to actually buy it because it is $5 but I've been playing it for 2 or 3 hours every day I still haven't reached the end I'm absolutely loving it and I cannot wait for more updates no regrets paying $5 probably the best game I ever paid $5 for On the App Store. üòáüòá

I really love this game but only one change... please make it so you live in a house not a cabin for dogs and if you win a race you can get furniture for your house also so that in your backyard orphaned dogs can wander in there to be rescued and then you can sort with them and new dog breeds EG chihuahua
I saw Stacy plays play this and loved it!
Different from most games. Nice mix of arcade game play, dogs and story telling. Total strategy looks to be layers deep.

How do you breed puppies on this game? I'm having a great time playing it and got it after I watched YouTube channels playing it. But breeding seems impossible. At first it said I needed 5 dogs, then 6 and now 7 dogs.
replyContent: You need 2 more dogs than the required number of your current league! So if you have climbed leagues, that's why the number goes up. Sorry for the lack of clarity!

content: Wasn't sure what to expect but the game is adorably entertaining
Gotta love dem dogs! Gameplay mechanic has to be discovered more than taught. It's challenging, but not brutally so. More dogs, more challenge.
This game is great for anyone! Even better if you love dogs. The way you race is fun and how you have to train the dogs is really cool. I would and will recommend it to friends
Love the game, it's so much fun! I found a bug too: Sometimes after a race the music cuts off while I'm my character's home. When it's fixed I'll change my rating to 5 stars!
Such a fun game!  The art details bring personality to your dogs and the environments. Fun game play, that can be challenging without being frustrating. Great soundtrack too!

content: This is a really enjoyable game. Gameplay is fairly simple but highly addictive, with a bit of strategy thrown in as well. Doesn't use much battery on my Shield K1 tablet. A few small glitches here and there, but nothing major that interrupts gameplay at all. Only request I'd make is added support for the Shield controller. I noticed some gamepad settings in the options menu, but nothing works with the Shield controller. Considering many gamers have this tablet, it would be a great thing to add. :)
Keeps crashing...REFUNDED
replyContent: Sorry to hear it was crashing, Tony. There were some issues with the save syncing systems that I hope I've alleviated with the past few updates, plus a few other stray issues. If you choose to give it another go, I hope it helps!

content: Sometimes during racing it lags a lot. It's also a major battery waster. Other than this, it's a pretty great game, and exactly what I expected. There's some nice diversity on the types of dogs you can get, as usually with these games it's only Malamutes and Huskies, but this game has Labs, Samoyeds, Schnauzers, and probably some other breeds I overlooked that normally aren't considered sledding breeds. (Also, love the "hire a new dog" and breeding component. Without it, it'd get pretty boring.)
It's more fun than it looks! Played it for like 8 hours straight.
I got the game to start and played it a little but the screen will go blank while playing.
I met the developers at PAX WEST, they were both really nice. I'm proud of you guys you made an awesome game. It's really fun and relaxing. This will make my morning bus trips more enjoyable!
This really is fun. If you love dogs you'll enjoy it even more.
